<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 18 at 3:54PM EST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Blowing Snow Likely in Open Areas through Tonight...
* WHAT...At least patchy blowing and drifting snow caused by
southwest wind gusts to 35 mph this afternoon and northwest
wind gusts to 40 mph tonight.
* WHERE...Open or rural areas of east-central Illinois and
northwest Indiana.
* WHEN...Through tonight.
* IMPACTS...Reduced visibility and lightly snow covered roads due
to blowing and drifting snow, making for locally hazardous
travel.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A Winter Weather Advisory may be needed if
blowing snow is expected to become more widespread and
hazardous.
* ACTIONS...Allow extra travel time and expect varying road
conditions and visibility in open areas.</description>
